text:
he sat beside me above the waters last spring and told me,"you know, for a change, you should try loving yourself." and i laughed really hard at him. he looked me in the eye and i asked him,"what does that mean? there is something sacred about the love you recieve from your beloved." he looked at me, the sunlight touched his tired eyes, drawing wrinkles around the corners. he let out a little smile, i could see one of his crooked teeth between his lips, and he looked away. he holds my hand more firmly, and lets out a sigh. and i recognise that sigh, the one filled with sorrow and loss. he looks back at me and says, "all that time i kept chasing love in my youth, just like you, and nothing fulfilled me, all the love i gave or got. and i realised nothing gives you more happiness than working on yourself, and solitude gave me that opportunity." i never understood what he meant, until the last few months. loving yourself seems so ordinary, that's why we find ourselves clueless when it comes to that. it's maintaining boundaries you once erased because you gave into the person you thought was home. it's giving yourself the liberty to make mistakes, eat the sugary snack you've been craving, go for a run, or just waste time alone, by yourself. it's knowing you owe yourself the same time and care you so easily give away, and also knowing people will point fingers at you once you make them feel a little less entitled, once you remove them from that throne, they will label you selfish, but self love will teach you to be okay with that. you deserve space. you deserve time. and the person you deserve it from the most is, definitely, you.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
"if power mainly resides with men, what does this imply for accountability? if the world is unfair, who is responsible for making it right? this cannot be a burden just for women. we men must play an active role in ensuring a more just world. we men must not only be part of gender equality, not just a conversation, but the solution. we men must defy the structures of patriarchy and the outdated notions of manhood and use that questioning to build more justice societies."
_
powerful speech by @winstoncduke at the @heforshe impact summit, @unitednations

text:
just wanted to let you know, to whoever is going through some trauma, a tragic loss, growing pains, or is not happy with where they are in life right now. god will see you through it, you will get out of this rut. life sucks terribly sometimes but it’s up to you, whether you drown or reach shore. i’m living proof of that, trust me getting to this spot was not easy and i’m not even close to shore yet but i’m liking this stronger, patient and different version of me.
stick to your circle, love you completely and align your dreams with your goals so they can become reality. it’s not easy, there’s days that you will have to fight harder. but if you fight, and stay on task it will work out. 
you got this! 
believe in yourself.
love yourself.
invest in your dreams.

dearest self.... feliz 2ndo aniversario - ❤️ eres una gran guerrera. you are at peace, you got this. keep going.
❤️

text:
good morning everyone! how are you? it's been a while. i'm doing well. i'm in saigon still. i'm working on my book and health. i'm feeling great and honestly better than i have in probably 6 years. good things are happening. 
as many of you know, i have been through a lot in my life. a lot of it i share openly but somethings i still can't, and that's why i decided to write a book about my life. in the process of writing over the last few months, i have garnered a sense of peace that i have never experienced. in the process of writing, i have laughed, cried, been angry, felt helpless, and wanted to scream at the world. i've also felt empowered, brave, secure, and capable.  many of these emotions i haven't felt so viscerally in my life. 
it dawned on me that like in my youth writing is one of the most cathartic things for me. as an adult and a survivor of horrific trauma, some self-inflicted but most of it at the hands of adults, it hit me like a brick that writing is still a compelling mechanism for me. 
as i sat up watching the red sunrise a couple of weeks ago in thailand, it hit me that i wanted to give other people the same outlet that i have been utilizing and i came up with @traumaletters

www.traumaletters.com is a site that i built that is for anonymous creative letter writing for anything including but not limited to trauma around child abuse, sexual abuse, domestic violence, sex, drugs, addiction, and suicide. the letters are both good and evil and there is no wrong or right. the site is only a week old, but i don't believe in waiting for things to be perfect before sharing them with the world. that said, i hope that you will check out #traumaletters share it on your page, and maybe even submit your own anonymous letter. i also welcome any thoughts or suggestions that you have as this is not about me and i want this to be a platform utilized by anyone that needs it. so if you have ideas, please message me.

i also want to take a moment and say thank you to everyone who has ever had my back. i am so lucky to have friends like you, and i am appreciative of you. 
have an amazing day and remember that you can do anything.

text:
"beauty to me"  when i was younger i used to think my beauty was measured by the neatness of my hair, the colour of my eyes, the colour of my nails, having the least amount of noticed pores on my face, and my hip to bust ratio. *

i was taught, that my beauty was measured by the amount of melanin in my skin, the elasticity and length of my curls, my height in heels. the amount of jewelry i wore, the quality of my clothing. the amount of curse words i used, the way i crossed my legs when i sat. my legs in a skirt, and of course my hip to bust ratio. *

today i know beauty is immeasurable, and beauty is as simple as a genuine smile, or the glisten of eyes caught in the sunlight. the crazed eyes caused from passion and the feeling i evoke in the people around me. *

photography by: @moemaureen

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
refuse to be silenced
__________________
if you’ve been around me, chances are you know that i have a lot of strong opinions  that often go against the ‘crowd’. and i’m not afraid to passionately share what i think. that comes from experience, regret, success and having strong women in my life. it also comes from the fact that for too long, women have been told to be quiet. many of our girls have been told that in order to get a man, you have to be quiet, soft, agreeable and keep your opinions to yourself. that messaging unfortunately translates to girls not feeling their voice or opinions are valued, and so they are silent when it’s time to speak up in class, they are silent when they need to communicate with their parents and too often, they are silent, when they are victims of sexual harassment or assault. and in many ways society is still telling women to be quiet... when it comes to our bodies or our stories of harassment and abuse. that is why i applaud #metoo and #timesup and the women’s marches, because it is time that we have a stronger voice in the conversations that matter and that our voice be respected. 
so if you are like me... strong, outspoken and opinionated... don’t worry about dimming your light to be more attractive or likable. like yourself. love yourself. be yourself. and while you are at, let them know that you are here. 
now go on and have yourself a great day! 😘
#mindfulmonday

text:
an act of courage is most likely identified as such after the act, when the dust settles and you have time to think about it in the larger context. at the moment the decision is simply to act or not. such was my experience about 10 years ago when some folks asked me to help a black woman who had been stopped for speeding on her way home from her nursing assistant's job. the incident escalated and resulted in her being arrested on several felonies, the facts of which seemed unjustified. 
over the next year i led a group of white and black, male and female, community members to challenge law enforcement's "blue wall" protecting the office, to show up at court hearings, hold rallies, to stand on the steps of prescott's courthouse to show support and seek justice for her.  a jury found her guilty, but the judge, we think, saw the problem for what it was and gave her no jail time and unsupervised probation.

today she is a successful nurse, but it took years for her to get her rights back and her record completely cleared as though the nightmare never happened. getting involved in such a case had its risks for all of us in a state with little diversity tolerance. it was a great example that when we stand together for justice, we win. ***submit your story of courage here: http://illuminatefilmfestival.com/acts-of-courage-form 
#1000actsofcourage
#thischangeseverything
#illuminatefilmfestival

#blacklivesmatter #womensreality #metoo #everydaysexism #fem2 #feminism #feminist #actofcourage

text:
debunking some sexual harassment myths:
1️⃣ both men and women can be harassed.
2️⃣ illegal sexual harassment can occur between people of the same sex.
3️⃣ sexual harassment can occur outside of the workplace if behavior happens at a work-related event.
4️⃣ supervisors or those in authority positions are not the only ones who can be harassers. you can be harassed by a coworker and, in some cases, a third party such as an agent or client of your employer.

#iamfearless #courageous #notme #sexualharassment #discussion #metoo #harassment #workplace #notmevoice #breakthesilence #reportit #clearcommunications #takeaction #startaconversation #hr #humanresources #employees #officelife

text: law school is extremely triggering (reference to se/ual a/sau/t) you will have to defend people you don’t particularly agree with. you have no choice really (in general). every week we are given a few scenarios to prepare for. this week we are told to defend a mr michael oakley who went clubbing and grabbed a woman’s breasts aka sexually assaulted her. now here i am; an advocate for human rights (yes i am aware everyone has a right to fair trail and having a barrister helps with fair hearings) and someone who speaks up against sexual assault almost every single second of my life, and i’m placed in a position where i’m trying to figure out a way to argue that my client reasonably believed mrs dawson had consented to being touched in that way! so kids- it is upon you (defendant) to determine whether the victim has consented or not. ask her/him/them if they are consenting. it will protect people from being sexually violated, it will protect you from litigation and it will avoid us lawyers the pain and emotional/mental anguish of trying to defend you and it will certainly help keep our anxiety at bay. 👩🏻‍⚖️ 👩🏻‍⚖️👩🏻‍⚖️👩🏻‍⚖️👩🏻‍⚖️#lawschool #barstudent #sexualassault #metoo #consent #criminallaw #criminallawyers #nomeansno #lawblogger #thisisnotconsent
name: Maham Mustafa Pirbhoy

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
dailyhunt

-

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text: today we honor tarana burke, a civil rights activist and founder of the #metoo movement. tarana burke grew up in the bronx, new york and graduated from aurburn university. she founded the "just be" non-profit focused on the wellness of black girls in alabama and created the #metoo movement in 2006 to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual assault or abuse. this movement gained a larger following in 2017 after the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations. tarana burke is currently the senior director at girls for gender equity in brooklyn. #genderresoucesccny #cuny #ccny #blackhistorymonth #metoo

text:
#блог
⠀
апскертинг и брекзит
⠀
начало года в лондоне впечатлило сразу несколькими общественными событиями, микс которых совершенно характерен для этого города с практически абсолютной внутренней (и внешней) свободой, короче говоря, полезные новости.
⠀
1. благодаря очередному усилению активности угрей, в темзе обнаружили очередное повышенное содержание кокаина, продукта его метаболизма и кофеина. именно эта смесь влияет на гиперактивность будущего кулинарного деликатеса, которая мешает популяции размножаться. в лондоне – самый высокий (и это исторически) в европе уровень потребления кокаина. и если в других городах британии он снижается в будни и повышается в уик-энды, то в столице является постоянной величиной и не зависит от дня недели. между тем темза считается одной из самых чистых европейских рек – в нее вернулись даже морские коньки и дельфины. и экологов гораздо больше кокаина волнуют горы пластика на помойках и использованные влажные салфетки, которые забивают промышленные фильтры сточных вод.
⠀
2. теперь и в англии (8 лет назад – в шотландии) апскертинг («под юбку» в примерном переводе) признан уголовно наказуемым преступлением. апскертинг (в сетях – апскирт) – это фотографирование или видеосъемка женщин снизу без их согласия с целью получить снимки или видео нижнего белья. как правило, это происходит в метро и других видах общественного транспорта, в ночных клубах. в петербурге осенью была предпринята акция против апскертинга. но поскольку она была довольно тупой, то и цели своей практически не достигла. акции протеста тоже надо уметь делать. а вот в одном из американских штатов законодательно запрещено женщинам носить лакированную обувь, так как в ней может отражаться нижнее белье.
⠀
3. во время чемпионата англии по футболу на поле внезапно выбежал кот... продолжение на сайте: https://nanevskom.ru/apskerting-i-brekzit/
⠀
#лондон #скандал #интрига #британия #greatbritain #англия #черныйкот #юбка #metoo #bafta #брайансингер #bryansinger #football #футбол #ситуация #питерonline #питерlive #like #журналистынеспят #словоневоробей #актуальноечтиво #nanevskom

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
#bali has had already hundreds (or thousands) issues with women being chased, sexually harassed, insulted physically and emotionally. some of my girlfriends had this issue twice, no matter if it happened on their way home from dinner or even during the day while jogging on the streets.

of course, all of the women directly contacted the police and local administration (banjar), unfortunately, they don’t want to do anything about it and always find an excuse to blame the women themselves.

we’ve had enough, bali is amazing and all of us consider it as our home, we want it to be safe.

we’ve kept the silence but this snowball has to start moving. right now a team of girls working on spreading the word in public media, our goal is to wake up the minds of bali government, especially in #canggu, so they can finally do some actions to protect their tourists and make their paradise safe again.

dear friends, please help us to sign this petition (link on my profile) and spread the word, we can’t sit and look at this anymore! @makerswomen 
#safetyinbali #balibesafe #womenharassment #womensafety #indonesiantourism #balitourism #canggu #internationalsafety #canggu #bali #metoo #stopsexualassault #makebalisafe #wedeservebetter #itsneverokay #pleasestop #makerswoman #stopsexualharassment #balilife #balidaily #guguide

text:
a movie that speaks to the effects of childhood trauma, how the #metoo movement has always been the truth...
the stats are 1:3 women have been sexually assaulted/abused and 1:5 boys. the 
as a trauma specialist, i can say that it’s more then that...it’s about 75% of the population that has experienced either overt or covert abuse. children deserve better.
be the adult who does better.
#bethechange #endtraumacycles #epigenetics #acestudy 
remember 
that underneath a defensive exterior is a wound it’s protecting..
that the presentation is a cover for what couldn’t be expressed with safety...
that sex most often isn’t even about sex...
that struggles are about unearthing the deep seeded root of something seeking the light.
truth does set you free...
healing transforms pain into wisdom.
we appreciate all the actors who showed up to do this movie.

text:
🤔друзья или клиенты?🤔
⠀
совсем недавно в instagram появилась возможность делиться публикациями только с определённым кругом лиц.😏
⠀
разработчики предложили назвать раздел для избранных пользователей - “ лучшие друзья ”.⭐
⠀
мы же, в свою очередь, рекомендуем вам использовать эту полезную функцию не только для друзей, но и для постоянных клиентов.🔥
⠀
например, вы захотели поощрить своих избранных клиентов скидкой. просто добавьте всех выбранных вами пользователей в список ”лучших друзей ” и поделитесь сторис. публикация будет доступна только для них.💁♀
⠀
удобно и практично 🧚🏻♀
💁
💁
💁
⠀

text:
“i used a wood to kill her after several warnings for her to desist from taking calls from men in my house. i have been suspecting that my wife was sleeping around with other men in my village but in the heat of argument, i killed her. my late wife brought men into our matrimonial home and my culture abhors such an act; that was why i killed her to save the family from the shame,” -these are the words of 32-year-old jibrin abu. .
according to naijadiary.ng abu who hails from dabogi village in lapai, was arrested by the niger state police in nigeria for allegedly beating his wife, victoria, to death with a piece of wood over allegations that she cheated on him. .
reports confirm that abu, after killing his wife, attempted to commit suicide by drinking "sniper" insecticide, but his attempt failed as he was rushed to the lapai general hospital by police operatives and was treated. .
he is said to be tried in court soon.
.

text:
"la calunnia è un venticello...."
la mia vita continua,anche se in questi giorni ho dovuto subire,come donna,delle molestie e del cyber bullismo. #metoo
mi sono dovuta scusare con chi amo di cose che non ho mai fatto,con chi lavoro di comportamenti che non ho mai tenuto, 
ma che anche se avessi fatto,sarebbero dovute rimanere intime e riservate.
e' già lontano,per tutti gli internetnauti,il ricordo di #tizianacantone e del male che si può fare con la "calunnia".
io,fortunatamente,non ero la protagonista di quel video che qualcuno,per suo piacere,mi ha voluto etichettare con allusioni squallide e foto di triangoli amorosi.
certo,se fossi stato uno di quegli uomini "preistorici" che affollano il web,avrei potuto anche vantarmi.
e invece no,eccomi donna,a subire anche io,le solite molestie maschiliste,inutili,fastidiose e anche patetiche,che nel 2019 non hanno veramente alcuna ragione di esistere.
ma come ho detto la vita continua. 
e continua il mio sorriso,la mia voglia di essere me stessa,di ballare,di cantare,di volare,e di recitare.
io so di credere in questo  mondo,io so di credere negli uomini e nelle donne moderne, oggi,come sempre,e non saranno pochi patetici imbecilli, 
che non hanno neanche il coraggio di metterci la faccia,a fermare la mia spensieratezza.
#valentinamarconi
#lareginadellamortadella
😔❤️

text:
the rise of #metoo has empowered survivors of sexual harassment and assault, especially students on college campuses, to come forward with allegations. 
social media can often be a powerful tool for spreading useful information, assuring people that they are not alone, and raising awareness about important issues.

however, the necessity of creating tangible change and providing real support to people affected by these issues can not be overlooked.
“social media is a great tool. but a hashtag is not a movement. part of movement building is that it can’t solely live online. you have to get in the community and look people in their eyes and tell them, ‘we need you.’” -tarana burke (founder of #metoo)
[https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2018/12/14/2018-title-ix-report/]

text:
one of my biggest frustrations as a christian woman battling lust was a lack of biblical and actionable resources showing me how to embrace sexual purity. i didn't need another sermon on "avoiding sexual sin," i needed to know how to get out of it.

my name is titania paige, and the purpose in purity podcast exists because through the loving pursuit of god i found wholeness in christ. he delivered me from pornography, masturbation, ungodly relationships, and same-sex attraction. i want others to experience the same transformation i have through my relationship with christ. that's why i'm here. 😊 
but don't get me wrong. i'm still on the journey!

shock is going through the hip hop community once again as #ajcalloway is accused of sexual assault for what seem. the host of #extra has been suspended from the program after multiple women accused him of sexual assault. #warnerbros has since officially confirmed the decision in a statement saying the network has started an internal investigation into all of the misconduct claims. calloway has been the host of “extra” for over a decade, and this wasn’t the first time he’s been caught facing the same charges. in 2006, he was arrested for alleged sexual assault on activist #sillaiabrams. the case was later dismissed “on procedural grounds,” but abrams maintains the assault did in fact take place. many more women have taken the same stand against a. j, lodging their own complaints of sexual assault. one of the women stated that due to his status and fame she was afraid to come forward and tell her story. in the heat of the scandal, his lawyer released a statement saying, “mr. calloway maintains that these unsubstantiated allegations are patently false. he vehemently denies that he ever assaulted anyone and looks forward to clearing his name.” looks like he was caught,l up to his old tricks again but we will keep you updated on the details on the case this time around. what are your thoughts on this story? comment below, it’s monday!

text:
mariam goes to school.

2 weeks ago, during our vocational and skills training session in oke ira, badore, mariam's mother told the team that out of 6 children, only her boys (3 of them) go to school. the girls do not go to school because her family can't afford to send all of them, so her husband decided that only the males will go to school.

today we have enrolled one of the girls (mariam) to school. unfortunately, her sisters are in their late teens and they won't be able to cope but mariam is 5 years old.

mariam wore her new uniform and screamed excitedly and she is full of thanks.

this isn't going to be an easy journey for mariam. mariam is older than her classmates, she doesn't understand a word in english or yoruba, she can't identify figures or numbers but it will be worth it.

that girl is a fighter.

#education #educateher #metoo #womenempowerment #empowerment #sdg5 #sdg4

image description: pink pyramid with gradient of obstetric violence.

#repost @birthmonopoly with @get_repost
・・・
normalizing disrespect through jokes about birth plans is just one part of a culture where birthing people are disrespected in more explicit and serious ways. 📣
it's meaningful that this model comes from one originally created about rape culture. birth is where misogyny and inherent power dynamics meet over women's bodies--it just happens to be in a medical setting.
📣
what can we do about this? get on the waitlist for my #knowyourrights course coming out this week--packed with info to empower you and your clients about your rights in birth! waitlist: www.birthmonopoly.com/birth-rights
📣
[concept from and thanks to11thprincipleconsent.org/ consent-propaganda/rape-culture-pyramid"]

link in bio to hear why the term ‘toxic masculinity’ is so polarizing, and what gillette was hoping to achieve with their latest campaign ⬆️🎧

text: flo kennedy was an absolute badass civil rights advocate and our shero. not only was did she work to bring intersectional perspectives to the feminist and civil rights movements, she was a  fierce advocate for reproductive freedom, suing the roman catholic church for interference with abortion and organizing a group of feminist lawyers to challenge the constitutionality of new york state’s abortion law, helping influence the legalization of abortion in 1970. a legendary iconoclast who refused to be silenced or conform, she also led a “pee-in” at harvard to protest lack of female bathrooms on campus. that’s our kind of activist. happy birthday, flo kennedy! 💓

text:
aviation: precious minutes will pass (7/10) by nicholas jones, 10 january 2018. -

i know that you’ve been asking where i’ve been,
and here is the honest truth,
that i can’t come over for the sake of myself,
because i don’t want to hurt you,

precious minutes will pass between,
whenever i first get there - and whenever i eventually leave,
then you’ll ask me to stay,
with your heart on your sleeve and i just won’t know what to do,

because the part of me that loves you,
is the part of me that has to live without you. -

what she said -->reposted from @jacquereid -  refuse to be silenced
__________________
if you’ve been around me, chances are you know that i have a lot of strong opinions  that often go against the ‘crowd’. and i’m not afraid to passionately share what i think. that comes from experience, regret, success and having strong women in my life. it also comes from the fact that for too long, women have been told to be quiet. many of our girls have been told that in order to get a man, you have to be quiet, soft, agreeable and keep your opinions to yourself. that messaging unfortunately translates to girls not feeling their voice or opinions are valued, and so they are silent when it’s time to speak up in class, they are silent when they need to communicate with their parents and too often, they are silent, when they are victims of sexual harassment or assault. and in many ways society is still telling women to be quiet... when it comes to our bodies or our stories of harassment and abuse. that is why i applaud #metoo and #timesup and the women’s marches, because it is time that we have a stronger voice in the conversations that matter and that our voice be respected. 
so if you are like me... strong, outspoken and opinionated... don’t worry about dimming your light to be more attractive or likable. like yourself. love yourself. be yourself. and while you are at, let them know that you are here. 
now go on and have yourself a great day! 😘
#mindfulmonday - #regrann

dance was an instrumental part of my healing as i navigated my season of life with ptsd, panic attacks, and sleepless nights. overnight, i was forced to leave the naïveté of my invincibility behind. i became a part of a terrifying national statistic: one in five women who have been raped in their lifetimes. i became another voice adding to the chorus of “me too”s. when words failed to make sense of that season, dance was there. that’s why i have included dance as an important symbol of healing in my upcoming music video for “la paz.” thank you to @richiwangbang for learning and performing my choreography with so much emotion, and for partnering with me to bring the essence of this song to life. “la paz” music video coming 2/22. 🙏 .

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
ich bin heute so ergriffen von diesem alltagshelden, den ich gleichzeitig meinen freund nennen darf, dass ich das einfach mit euch teilen mag❤️ das ist julian. julian ist dieses jahr karnevalsprinz. das war schon von klein auf sein traum. auch wenn es bedeutet über 2 monate jedes wochenende von berlin nach fulda zu pendeln um das ganze wochenende von einem event zum anderen zu tingeln. warum er das macht, war mir zunächst nicht klar, doch jetzt weiß ich, er hatte eine mission. hier ein auszug aus seiner selbst verfasste büttenrede, für dessen inhalte er sogar in der tageszeitung gelandet ist. an diesem punkt geht es um die vermehrten afd plakate in seiner heimat: “ein anderes plakat dagegen war richtig,
sicherheit für frauen und töchter- denn das ist wichtig.
denn nicht nur in hollywood geht es wild zu,
auch hier riefen frauen jetzt öfter #metoo.

und viele der grabscher sehn ausländisch aus,
drum schreien jetzt noch mehr „ausländer raus“
und ja – es klingt vielleicht auch etwas barsch,
doch – wer frauen antatscht, der is halt ein arsch.

und die gibt es tatsächlich überall,
grabscher sind quasi international,

auch ich finde: fremde fummler sind hier nicht willkommen
doch was ist mit denen, die schon von hier kommen?
die gern moralapostel miemen,
bei den grabschenden muslimen.

die zum saufen und grabschen auf volksfeste reisen,
in thailand und auf malle moralisch entgleisen,
und auch zu haus gern auf menschenwürde scheißen,
können wir die nicht auch irgendwohin ausweisen?

aber ne, die bleiben und wolln sich vermehren,
sie wolln patrolieren in bürgerwehren,
und hauen was anders aussieht zu pamp
und könnten sie, wählten sie auch den trump.

ja auch hier wächst das bedürfnis nach waffen
wie solln wir das hier bloß zivilisiert schaffen?
kommt das, wird auch noch andres beschlossen,
und der demokratie in den rücken geschossen.
mit unseren eigenen panzern und gewehren,
die den global frieden – seien wir ehrlich – erschweren.

es brodelt in der ganzen welt,
die erde braucht jetzt einen held.
eine idee, um hass zu bekämpfen,
und friede bringt für alle menschen.

ich glaube ich hab da die lösung parat,
und die meistert wirklich mal jeden spagat: ⬇️

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
i wanted to make this drawing about few months ago and i finally did. based on my experience hooking up with a possibly narcissist, and in this drawing i illustrate what is being in a relationship with one. a relationship full of lies, deceit, betrayals, pain, abuse, manipulation, confusion etc, even thought, at the beginning everything seems perfect and unreal, like, "too perfect to be truth". you feel sick, anxious, fear, depresed, confused, madness, weak, tired...also you get to feel like the biggest fool in the world for all the shit you did just to keep that person happy, a person who never cared about you in first place, a person who never existed either, a person that only wants to feed from you meanwhile you are getting weaker every second you are with them. so now, i made this drawing to close definitely this chapter of my life, let it completly go and do not touch the subject ever again, and better focus on myself and heal from all this mess, at least it didn't got "too far" , so i can heal more quickly, but i kinda feel guilty and dirty . my advice is, be sure to meet very well that person before starting a relationship, love yourself cuz if not, you will only bring tóxic relationship to your life and you deserve more than that, you deserve better, not a person that treats you like a piece of shit. also be alert to the red flags, so you can leave on time and save yourlsef. love y'all💕 . ~song: distant traces of beauty - ace attorney ost

i wanted to make this drawing about few months ago and i finally did. based on my experience hooking up with a possibly narcissist, and in this drawing i illustrate what is being in a relationship with one. a relationship full of lies, deceit, betrayals, pain, abuse, manipulation, confusion etc, even thought, at the beginning everything seems perfect and unreal, like, "too perfect to be truth". you feel sick, anxious, fear, depresed, confused, madness, weak, tired...also you get to feel like the biggest fool in the world for all the shit you did just to keep that person happy, a person who never cared about you in first place, a person who never existed either, a person that only wants to feed from you meanwhile you are getting weaker every second you are with them. so now, i made this drawing to close definitely this chapter of my life, let it completly go and do not touch the subject ever again, and better focus on myself and heal from all this mess, at least it didn't got "too far" , so i can heal more quickly, but i kinda feel guilty and dirty . my advice is, be sure to meet very well that person before starting a relationship, love yourself cuz if not, you will only bring tóxic relationship to your life and you deserve more than that, you deserve better, not a person that treats you like a piece of shit. also be alert to the red flags, so you can leave on time and save yourlsef. love y'all💕 . ~song: distant traces of beauty - ace attorney ost

text:
first week back in id. what does this mean? 👇
•
it’s where i get to be “full” clinical again, looking after inpatients on a ward with complex infections, hiv, tb, endocarditis, resistant bugs, the “weird-and-often-not-wonderful-for-the-patient” infections that got me interested in this as a medical specialty. my first day also involved having a hanger thrown at me but we’re all friends now! 😜👩🏻‍⚕️
•
it’s also international day of women and girls in science. walking down the corridor, wearing this outfit, a male member of staff wheeling a patient looked me up and down, winked at me and said, “if i ran the hospital, i’d make all women wear boots like that...” as he was wheeling a patient, i bit my lip from shouting “#metoo 🤬” but it’s a sorry reminder of how some people think that demeaning intelligent women somehow makes them charming. 🤦🏻‍♀️
•
rather than just moan though, i’d encourage you to check out *some* of the accounts of inspiring female #scicommers on here by tapping the tags on this post. there are obviously more and also ace male ones too! happy science day! 🥰 •
#womenempowerment #peopleempowerment #womeninscience #womeninmedicine #boss #workstyle #infectiousdiseases #infection #microbiology #physician #medicine #medical #medscilife #tb #hiv #sepsis #stethoscope
name: Dr Farah S. Medical Doctor, UK

text:
hi friends! i am so excited to introduce clara wisner of @revolutionarylifestyle to you. remember back in january when you voted on which webinar topic you wanted to hear? well clara will be talking about trauma & body image on march 5 at 6pm mst.

in this webinar nutritionist and psychotherapist clara wisner will be exploring the relationship between physical and emotional trauma and negative body image. from disordered eating to body dysmorphia, experiencing trauma is a factor in how we heal and get to a place of food freedom and body peace. 
in this webinar you will learn: 
1. 5 steps to stop hating your body right now.
2. how past trauma or abuse contributes to body image issues + disordered eating.
3. the 3 best tools to use daily to love yourself more and feel more comfortable in your body.

we can't wait to  see you there! please register for this webinar. 👉 link in bio. dm me with any questions you have.

#weareher #revolutionarylifestyle #trauma #bodyimage #bodypositive #survivorsisters #toxicrelationships #heal #empower #restore #webinar #metoo #nomore #loveyourself #bodypositivity

text:
"collective action and shared responsibility for driving gender parity is what makes international women's day successful"

did you know?
"international women's day (march 😎 is a global day celebrating the social, economic, cultural and political achievements of women. the day also marks a call to action for accelerating gender parity. international women's day (iwd) has occurred for well over a century, with the first march 8 iwd gathering supported by over a million people in austria, denmark, germany and switzerland. prior to this the socialist party of america, united kingdom's suffragists and suffragettes, and further groups campaigned for women equality. today, iwd belongs to all groups collectively everywhere. iwd is not country, group or organisation specific. make iwd your day! - everyday!

how are will you be celebrating international women's day this year? get involved and/or join us:

i'm excited to speaking at the #internationalwomensday hosted by #womeninhealthcareuk in #leeds #weethood this year. #iwd #iwd2018 #pressforprogress #metoo #timesup #womeninbusiness #womenempowerment #womensmarch #beboldforchange

text:
i really loved #christine armstrong’s brilliantly honest article in the @thestmagazine yesterday about the growing elephant in the office that is workplace resentment between the sexes..... .
it really echoes a lot of what i’ve been hearing from my local flexible working community over the last couple of months. .
flexible working is a work pattern that employers are prepared to consider - it’s been reported that 68% of mums make a request for at least one type for flexible working practice, and in the majority they are approved.  great stats right?  not entirely......
.

most employers know that flexible working encourages business benefits including staff retention and motivation but what they really are still not getting right is the culture needed for flexible working to work.
.
the article yesterday quoted some pretty depressing stats around this; -18% is the percentage by which working mothers are more stressed than other people. -21% fewer woman work in full-time executive roles at ftse250 firms in 2018 than in 2017. -one of the most alarming stats quoted was that 16% of male managers hesitate to mentor a woman - this is three times higher than before the #metoo movement 🙀
.

something needs to change and change quickly to ensure that the resentment gap doesn’t grow any wider..... there needs to be open, honest conversations within the workplace and a shift away from flexible working being only a ‘female thing’. only when everyone involved starts being honest about life reality can it really be a success 👊🏻
.

text:
depuis #balancetonporc#metoo je vois une effervescence de mouvements qui concernent les violences faites aux femmes et c’est une grande avancée.✔️
mais aujourd'hui le viol masculin est trop sous peu représenté, on ne parle pas assez de cette réalité, ni de cette possibilité qu’ont les hommes de se faire agresser, violer.
les voix masculines autour des violences faites aux hommes ne sont pas assez représentés, les hommes ne parlent pas. 
pourtant cela existe et même si c’est une minorité par rapport aux violence faites aux femmes, nous ne pouvons pas la considérer comme moins importante.✔️
c’est un cercle vicieux: plus on minimalise les faits -> moins on en parle -> moins les victimes en parlent -> moins ils sont pris au sérieux. et puis finalement ça devient inexistant aux yeux des victimes et des agresseurs: "le viol masculin n’existe pas".✔️
nous devons prendre conscience qu’un homme peut aussi être brisé, vulnérable, qu’il n’est pas insatiable et que virilité ne rime pas avec performance sexuelle. avant d’être hommes nous sommes des individus.✔️
mais les hommes sont ils vraiment conscients qu’ils peuvent être violés ? sont t-ils conscients qu’ils ont le droit de le dénoncer ? sont ils conscients que si leur opposition verbale et physique n’est pas prise en compte par la personne d’en face, cette personne n’est plus une personne mais un agresseur.se sexuel.le? sont ils conscients qu’ils sont en droit de refuser un rapport sexuel ?✔️
en outre il faut savoir que les hommes violés sont majoritairement violés par des hommes.✔️
mais finalement les femmes sont elles conscientes de tous leurs actes ? ne sont- elles pas conditionnées à croire que les hommes sont des prédateurs sexuels, insatiables?
sont- elles vraiment conscientes qu’elles peuvent être des agresseuses sexuelles ?
pareillement, les hommes sont ils conscients que les femmes peuvent être des agresseuses sexuelles ? 
on conditionne les femmes à se méfier des violeurs en adoptant des comportements pour ne pas être des victimes mais on ne dit jamais aux femmes qu’elles peuvent être, elles aussi des violeuses. comme on ne dit jamais aux hommes qu’ils peuvent être victimes de violences sexuelles.
name: ÊTRE UN "HOMME" ?
tweet_full:
depuis #balancetonporc#metoo je vois une effervescence de mouvements qui concernent les violences faites aux femmes et c’est une grande avancée.✔️
mais aujourd'hui le viol masculin est trop sous peu représenté, on ne parle pas assez de cette réalité, ni de cette possibilité qu’ont les hommes de se faire agresser, violer.
les voix masculines autour des violences faites aux hommes ne sont pas assez représentés, les hommes ne parlent pas. 
pourtant cela existe et même si c’est une minorité par rapport aux violence faites aux femmes, nous ne pouvons pas la considérer comme moins importante.✔️
c’est un cercle vicieux: plus on minimalise les faits -> moins on en parle -> moins les victimes en parlent -> moins ils sont pris au sérieux. et puis finalement ça devient inexistant aux yeux des victimes et des agresseurs: "le viol masculin n’existe pas".✔️
nous devons prendre conscience qu’un homme peut aussi être brisé, vulnérable, qu’il n’est pas insatiable et que virilité ne rime pas avec performance sexuelle. avant d’être hommes nous sommes des individus.✔️
mais les hommes sont ils vraiment conscients qu’ils peuvent être violés ? sont t-ils conscients qu’ils ont le droit de le dénoncer ? sont ils conscients que si leur opposition verbale et physique n’est pas prise en compte par la personne d’en face, cette personne n’est plus une personne mais un agresseur.se sexuel.le? sont ils conscients qu’ils sont en droit de refuser un rapport sexuel ?✔️
en outre il faut savoir que les hommes violés sont majoritairement violés par des hommes.✔️
mais finalement les femmes sont elles conscientes de tous leurs actes ? ne sont- elles pas conditionnées à croire que les hommes sont des prédateurs sexuels, insatiables?
sont- elles vraiment conscientes qu’elles peuvent être des agresseuses sexuelles ?

text: @beyond50percent2019 will officially open on saturday 9 march from 2pm at #backspacegallery in #ballarat. this exhibition explores art made for social change to #end violence against women. artists have been #activists #feminists #agitators and #disrupters creating art that demands change, exposing the inequality in our social and political cultures, telling the stories that are often silenced, since the 1960’s and some would argue before that. beyond 50% examines the work made by international and australian artists who are operating in the #metoo era, activating for change through their art practice. @talfitzpatrick @catherinegomersall @aldonakmiec @panmelacastro @priyashakti @upsetting_rape @beyondempathy curated by me with the suppport of @artgalbal and @cityofballarat. join us in the conversation #genderequality #activistart #craftivism #change

text:
churches, please read and heed these wise words from al mohler's response to the houston chronicle's #scbtoo report (pictured: https://albertmohler.com/2019/02/11/reality-sexual-abuse-hits-home-happened-now/).⠀
.⠀
they justify concerns expressed by rachael denhollander in response to sgc: ⠀
"in their response, sgc claims that no third-party independent review is necessary because, among other things, covenant life church (clc) commissioned an independent investigation into how matters were handled. while the sgc statement simply describes clc as “a church that was then part of sovereign grace,” clc was in fact the flagship church of the denomination. furthermore, cj mahaney was the lead pastor at the time nearly all the alleged mishandlings of abuse at clc took place, including the abuses perpetrated by nathaniel morales. because the sgc statement relies heavily on the conclusions of this independent review, it bears further scrutiny here. there are several aspects which ought to have been disclosed, related to this review. ...⠀
.⠀
"in short, the firm and investigators had none of the expertise normally required of any team charged with handling such an investigation. the firm used poor methodology. they chose not to speak with key witnesses, including those who had raised the allegations, and were not allowed to speak with others key witnesses, including leaders at sgm. further, as discussed below, they did not disclose key evidence and blatantly misrepresented additional key evidence. finally, they used attorney-client privilege as a shield against public accountability and refused to disclose evidence or even the final written report - save for an oral retelling of the report to the members of clc. (i have transcripts of this report and access to the audio recording, which was provided to me by survivors.)"⠀
.⠀
read her full statement: https://www.facebook.com/notes/rachael-denhollander/response-to-sovereign-grace-churches/1720170721396574/⠀
.⠀
#churchtoo #metoo #sbctoo

gözlerimizi qamaşmağa başlarken, obama girdi söze. “i̇ster country sevin,ister rep yada rock. ferq etmir. musiqi acılarımızı,ümüdlerimiz,xoşbextliklerimizi ve qürurumuzu bölüşmemizi temin edir.bir-birimizi duymağımıza,devet etmemize vesile olur.bize herşeyin bir önemi olduğunu gösterir.her hekayedeki seslerin, her notdakı musiqilerin...doğrudurmu xanımlar?”
bu sözleriyle ayaqda alqışlanan obama, önceki il başladılan #metoo herekatının bitmediyini de xüsusile vurğulamışdır.

text_retweet:
6 weeks pregnant signed off with stress, 3 kids, mortgage and faced with a compromise agreement or fight a corporates legal team. that 2003 and it’s still happening please see @pregnant_then_screwed call to action #repost @pregnant_then_screwed with @get_repost
・・・
the government has launched a consultation into the 3 month time limit to raise a tribunal claim for pregnant women and new mums - we need your help.

this is our chance to shout as loud as we can that women need greater access to justice. the idea that pregnant women and new mums can start a tribunal process within 3 months is utter insanity and it results in 0.6% of victims raising a claim. i was sacked when i was 4 months pregnant and a week later i discovered i was having a high risk pregnancy. the doctor said to me: 'whatever you do, dont get stressed.' the 3 month time limit forced me to choose between the health of my baby and accessing the justice i deserved.

i need you all to send an email to the people at beis so they know how important this is. the more emails they get, the more likely it is they will do something about this. i have even written the email for you so all you have to do is copy and paste. the link is in my bio. please comment below to say you have done it so we have an idea how many emails they get.

if you want to help ignite change, then now is your chance. 
big thanks to @olga.fitzroy for her help with this.
#givemesix #pregnantthenscrewed #metoo #timesup

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
the fourth edition of @lahootimelo took place in jamshoro. i went there on day 2 and i'm gonna share my thoughts on that now... this event was all about women, from liberation of women to #metoo movement from harassment stories to courageous acts. it is important to talk about all these sensitive topics and educate the masses about the steps they can take to protect them from all such cases. 
moreover, @sharmeenobaidchinoy
shared some of the amazing clips with us. ❤❤ and i also got a chance to see @evazubeck livee making her vlog 🙈😍 pakistani classical singer @maidhaiofficial also performed there, she was fantabulous. 🔥🔥🔥 eyyy how can i forget @fdvm the french dj duo... they have my heart! 😍😍😍😭😭😭😭 overall lahooti melo was fun bs hum thora jaldi chale gae the or kuch b nahi horha tha... 😐 
watch this 5 minutes vid to see what happened there 👀 thanks! .
.
.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
frankly, each of us has a responsibility to do our own work. when we are pointing fingers at someone else, it’s time to take a look at what our own crap and figure out what inside of us is causing us to point fingers in the first place.
♡
when you take a look at yourself and do the work you need to do to heal yourself, then you can’t help but become kinder, more loving and compassionate. and when you personally transform like that, from the inside, it does impact the world.
♡
imagine a world where we each did our work and became kinder, more loving and compassionate… we would have a kinder, more loving and compassionate world!
♡
do your work!
.
.
.
.
.

text:
long before #metoo, female artists were calling out sexual violence | vanderbilt news
#
photo courtesy vivian green frydsocial media has brought sexual assault into the public eye, but bearing witness to sexual violence in popular culture didn’t begin with the invention of tweets and posts, according to vanderbilt art history professor vivien green fryd. “what’s happening today with the metoo movement is a continuation of the feminist movement of the 1970s,” fryd said. “it was a time when female artists consciously began using their works to challenge social conceptions and the legal definitions of rape and incest in order to shift the dominant narrative of violence against women.” in her new book, against our will: sexual trauma in american art since 1970 (february 2019, penn state university press), fryd chronicles the evolution of this decades-long intervention through the lens of art history. she highlights feminist artists suzanne lacy, leslie labowitz, faith ringgold, judy chicago and kara walker, whose works sought to end the silence surrounding sexual violence. “it was a time when women began to use their art to express their own experiences with sexual violence, as well as challenge the male dominated art world,” fryd said. artists and art historians also began to more openly confront the works of masters like rubens…
link: https://metoozoo.com/news/long-before-metoo-female-artists-were-calling-out-sexual-violence-vanderbilt-news/

photo courtesy vivian green frydsocial media has brought sexual assault into the public eye, but bearing witness to sexual violence in popular culture didn’t begin with the invention of tweets and posts, according to vanderbilt art history professor vivien green fryd. “what’s happening today with the metoo movement is a continuation of the feminist movement of the 1970s,” fryd said. “it was a time when female artists consciously began using their works to challenge social conceptions and the legal definitions of rape and incest in order to shift the domit narrative of violence against women.” in her new book, against our will: sexual trauma in american art since 1970 (february 2019, penn state university press), fryd chronicles the evolution of this decades-long intervention through the lens of art history. she highlights feminist artists suzanne lacy, leslie labowitz, faith ringgold, judy chicago and kara walker, whose works sought to end the silence surrounding sexual violence. “it was a time when women began to use their art to express their own experiences with sexual violence, as well as challenge the male dominated art world,” fryd said. artists and art historians also began to more openly confront the works of masters like rubens…

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for paicular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in paicular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser repoed “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with ceain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a paicular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what repos often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robe mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political adveising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn
