wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin

text:
since valentine’s day is coming up this week i thought i would dedicate my posts to the occasion. today, i want to talk about consent. ❤️what is consent? ❤️
•
•
it is a voluntary agreement to engage in sexual activity of any kind, and it must be given freely. therefore, you cannot receive consent from someone who is intoxicated, unconscious or incapable of giving consent. additionally, consent is not freely given when you threaten others as well. remember a no means no. 
further, people can change their minds as well. they may have given consent 20 minutes ago, but maybe 20 minutes later they want to go get burgers instead. this means that they withdrew their consent and are no longer interested in engaging in any type of sexual activity. •
•
i wanted to talk about consent because according to statistics canada sexual assault is one of the most underreported crimes. this has a lot do with shame, guilt and stigma that is associated around it. this can happen to anyone, and it is so important that we are there for each other and supporting one another. movements like #metoo are important because they bring awareness to the issue. in fact, canada found that more people had started reported their sexual assaults to the police after the movement started. if someone is sexually assaulted they are more likely to have post-traumatic stress disorder (ptsd) which can impact many facets of their lives. further, someone who is sexually assaulted are 3 times more likely to have a major depressive episode. therefore, it is important that we provide support to individuals who have gone through sexual assault.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

in this home girls play with tools and boys play with dolls and carriages.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
in this week's love and hip hop: miami, jessie woo talks about being sexually assaulted and the other women on the show rallied around her in support. in a preview clip from the episode, trina has taken jessie, joy, and chinese kitty to an event at which #metoo founder tarana burke is speaking. “we spend most of our time trying to forget, but we recognize the pain. that's literally what metoo is — it's empowerment with empathy. 
__ in another preview of the episode, jessie confided in trina about her assault. jessie told trina that she was allegedly raped at an industry event. "as a rape victim, you feel like you’re powerless. you feel like you’re a loser–you feel so low. you feel like you don’t matter, she said.
__ in a 2018 cnn article titled “back from the brink of suicide, they want to save others” jessie was interviewed where she discussed being suicidal and knowing that someone loved her and cared about her is what kept her from ending her own life. that someone was her brother jeremy. "he talked me out of it, and that definitely was a turning point for me," said jessie. at the time, about five years ago, "i had dealt with someone raping me." the trauma of the rape, she said, was compounded with seeing that person excel professionally. "i just felt like i didn't want to be here anymore," she said. — earlier today, jessie tweeted, “on this day last summer, my abuser made the news. several women in the industry started coming forward with their stories of sexual assault. i thought i was the only one. i’m happy to say that i’m working with the lapd to help over a dozen other women put him behind bars #metoo. “i don’t think i’ll be watching this episode because i still have a lot of healing to do. but prayerfully, my testimony ministers to those of you who need it.”
__ we are sending hugs to jessie for being so brave to share her story with the world. hopefully, her story will help with her healing and help another victim who is struggling with coming forward. for more information on the meet visit metoomvmt.org.
__
🎥 @loveandhiphop | #lunionsuite #jessiewoo #lhhmia #meetoo #tarandaburke #haitianamerican

text:
standing up: a woman who claimed former melbourne lord mayor robert doyle inappropriately touched her at a dinner in 2016 has spoken publicly about it for the first time and is the first woman to make a formal complaint to police over his behaviour as lord mayor.
kharla williams, a real estate marketer who says mr doyle touched her inner thigh repeatedly while seated at the vip table of a dinner for state government agency melbourne health, said she had lost faith in the ability of the city of melbourne and the agency to resolve her complaint and made a statement to victoria police over the weekend.
the police are using the statement as the basis of a possible investigation into mr doyle, who is one of the most high-profile men in australia to fall from grace as a result of the #metoo movement.
‘the investigation that i trusted and had absolute faith in – in hindsight i would look back and think blind faith – is asking me, the victim, to be silent and basically go away.’ while kharla’s actions do kick robert doyle’s behaviour while lord mayor into the police/criminal realm for the first time, it remains to be seen what will happen. however, since this story ran in monday’s @financialreview, former premier and robert doyle friend jeff kennett has already apologised to her for his public criticisms of her complaint. #smallsteps

see bit.ly/kharla 📷 arsineh@arsineh.com

text: three billboards on sunset boulevard. the one in the foreground reads “in women we believe. then. now. always.” it is an advertisement celebrating the lifetime channel and its (mainly) female audience. the word ‘believe’ is made up of portraits of famous women, including the former first lady michelle obama. behind it a nine-storey high image of an attractive young woman, on her knees, staring longingly at her viewer, arching her back so that her pose emphasises her bottom, wearing just underwear. she feeds a kid some sort of vegetation. it reads “nice grass” and is an advertisement for the cannabis products brand, ignite. in the background is a billboard promoting comedy central’s tv program, “this is not happening”. a man, emerging from a hedge, holds a book with the word “shame” written on it. the byline reads “real stories. no morals.” an unusual triangle of synergy outside my hotel room that caught my eye today. los angeles, eh? hashtag me too; nice ass, kid; no morals; shame. #billboard #sunsetboulevard #losangeles #lifetime #ignite #comedycentral #sfmoma #synergy #contrast #la #iphoneonly #women #metoo #streetphotography #igers #igersla #iphonesia

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
not your regular transformation tuesday. but you'll never be able to heel if you don't close old wounds.
on the left i had just turned 13. this photo was a week before my mum died. 
whom i was the full time carer of for years.
i was living with my drug addict sister because id just been released from hospital after my first suicide attempt. my heart had stopped and id gotten so close to that light at the end of my dark life. 
i was defeated, mad, and hurting. ive got visible cuts on my arms. i was anorexic and had a death wish.
id already been raped, physically and emotionally abused, and had no idea by the time i was 25 id have of spent over 1 year combined in psyc wards, scars not even tattoos could hide and 8 suicide attempts under my sad little belt. 
i may not like myself now days, i may still be a very unwell person, some days i sit in the sun and think about how lucky i am, some days you'll find me curld up on the floor crying, taking every single bit left in me not to cut myself, or worse. i may hate my body and appearance, but it's so easy to forget where i came from. 
i was alone for so long, everyone had given up on me because it was too hard. 
but before anyone has a single thought of judgement in their minds about me i want everyone to know. 
i am a badass, i am a survivor, i am doing my absolute best.
and im proud of me, even on the days when no one else is. 💕

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
why do some leap ahead while others fall behind in our chaotic, connected age? innew power, jeremy heimans and henry timms confront the biggest stories of our time--the rise of mega-platforms like facebook and uber; the out-of-nowhere victories of obama and trump; the unexpected emergence of movements like #metoo--and reveal what's really behind them: the rise of "new power." for most of human history, the rules of power were clear: power was something to be seized and then jealously guarded. this "old power" was out of reach for the vast majority of people. but our ubiquitous connectivity makes possible a different kind of power. "new power" is made by many. it is open, participatory, and peer-driven. it works like a current, not a currency--and it is most forceful when it surges. the battle between old and new power is determining who governs us, how we work, and even how we think and feel.  new power shines fresh light on the cultural phenomena of our day, from #blacklivesmatter to the ice bucket challenge to airbnb, uncovering the new power forces that made them huge. drawing on examples from business, activism, and pop culture, as well as the study of organizations like lego, nasa, reddit, and ted, heimans and timms explain how to build new power and channel it successfully. they also explore the dark side of these forces: the way isis has co-opted new power to monstrous ends, and the rise of the alt-right's "intensity machine." in an era increasingly shaped by new power, this groundbreaking book offers us a new way to understand the world--and our role in it.

text:
everything is going to be ok because me too! 
so for christmas i got #girlwashyourface (and i’m almost done, for anyone who knows me this is a huge accomplishment) and omg i am obsessed with @msrachelhollis !! i jumped with 2 feet in to this books and all her wisdom! 
one of my goals for 2019 was to start listening to podcasts so obviously i started to mix in her rise (formally dias) pod cast on #spotify (*this is not an add just a true fan girl obsession). one quote that she has said in a few pod casts really caught my attention....
•
“c.s. lewis once said the most powerful words in the english language are me too”
•
when we put ourselves out there and simply say i’ll go first we encourage others to give it a try too! i’m loving how this @instagram community has become such a positive space for everyone to shout it from the roof top me too!!!!!! feeling happy, sad, mad, anxious, scared, not enough, lost, uninspired about something you will always find someone who feels the same, you might have to start it but it will always be followed by me too! 
#motivationmonday #healthinfocus #ygk #metoo #kingston

text:
#goodandmad: the revolutionary power of women's anger 
in the year 2018, it seems as if #womensanger has suddenly erupted into the public conversation. but long before pantsuit nation, before the women’s march, and before the #metoo movement, women’s anger was not only politically catalytic—but politically problematic. the story of #femalefury and its cultural significance demonstrates the long history of bitter resentment that has enshrouded women’s slow rise to political power in america, as well as the ways that anger is received when it comes from women as opposed to when it comes from men. 
with eloquence and fervor, rebecca tracks the history of #femaleanger as political fuel—from suffragettes marching on the white house to office workers vacating their buildings after clarence thomas was confirmed to the supreme court. here traister explores women’s anger at both men and other women; anger between ideological allies and foes; the varied ways anger is perceived based on its owner; as well as the history of caricaturing and delegitimizing female anger; and the way women’s collective fury has become transformative political fuel—as is most certainly occurring today. she deconstructs society’s (and the media’s) condemnation of female emotion (notably, #rage) and the impact of their resulting repercussions. 
highlighting a double standard perpetuated against women by all sexes, and its disastrous, stultifying effect, traister’s latest is timely and crucial. it offers a glimpse into the galvanizing force of women’s collective anger, which, when harnessed, can change history.
publisher: simon & schuster
publication date: october 2, 2018
#acpl #librarybooks #bibliophile #nonfiction
name: ChanWoo Rice Cray

text:
my story is a lot different than the others, i was not the victim, i was the one who tried to take advantage.
i had been talking to this guy for awhile, we met through mutual friends, and i found myself falling for him, he told me he felt the same.
he had disclosed to me during one of our conversations that he was a virgin, and had only kissed one other girl, i was not a virgin. 
one night when my mom was out i invited him over and we ended up drinking.
we started making out and then went up to my room. 
things got heavy and we were 69ing when i decided i wanted to have sex.
he told me he wasn’t ready, that he was good just doing oral, but i was drunk and coming on fairly aggressive.
i grabbed a condom from the nightstand and told him we were having sex, then i attempted to put it on him.
he went limp and said he had to go. 
we never really spoke again, when i should have at least apologized.
i have lived with that guilt for years.

text_retweet:
repost from @stephaniemonty.art  it's up on robertson x robertson in downtown culver city! go look at it! take pictures! spread it like wildfire and lets take these mfers down!! my loves, my friends, i haven't been very open about what happened last june. it took a long time for me to come around to find any response at all... i was convinced by my collaborative partner @trustyscribe. to take legal action even though i had no faith in it. i wasnt surprised when months went by and my story was still met with apathy by management, lawyers and the police.

even more months later we birthed the idea for this amazing art piece to retaliate and for me to take my power back in my most natural form of expression.

we all stand in solidarity in our collective trauma. i see us all standing tall and strong in the face of this 💪🏼 #amightyforce #metoo #metoomovement #streetart #streetartla

text:
i wanna take a minute to talk about hormonal birth control (which opens up a can of worms). it's tempting to pop a pill and cure a problem. take this and don't worry about getting pregnant! but in suppressing your moon cycle, what are you really doing? women are not designed to function like men: the same everyday. god designed us to have a week of blood, a week where we are forced to sit on the earth and be still. but in removing ourselves from the rhythm of nature, the essence of creation, our periods, that is exactly what we are doing. becoming more like men. we see where men are failing, so we have risen up to play roles that traditionally have belonged to them. earning money, being the head of the household, going to battle.
‧
in mainstream culture, we see focus on wounds of the divine feminine. #metoo movement, destruction of the earth, shaming sexuality. but the divine masculine has suffered and needs healing just as much. the wrongs done to the feminine are a result of the wounded masculine. homes without fathers, a culture that promotes a caricature of masculinity (money, alcohol, women, material things falsely equated with power), too much softness (in the mind, in the body), being shamed for expressing emotion, lack of connection to others (google "incels"). our ancestors went thousands of years bleeding every month. and now we expect to play god, literally stopping our blood, without suffering repurcussions? we are seeing lack of connection to the body, inability to tell who is a compatible genetic partner (google "birth control and divorce"), estrogen from pee that ends up in our drinking water, possible infertility once you stop using the pill...
‧
my heart goes out to women using bc and not giving it a second thought because they weren't informed. doctors prescribe bc for acne, or because periods are "annoying." periods should be celebrated as a time when the veil between spirit and material worlds is thin. pms is your intuition saying "if it's not a hell yes then it's a hell no." i am not doctor, but i have always believed in addressing the root of a problem, not the symptoms. i am passionate about this and happy to cont the convo 🙏🏼

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
these words have been leaping through my brain since the end of  last year. “you are not a victim for sharing your story...
you are a survivor setting the world on fire with your truth.” i had been battling with the decision to speak about other parts of my story. to allow my nakedness of past trauma to flood your squares. but time and again i kept saying nope, i’m not ready. i’m still doing the healing. it wasn’t until this last month that i think after decades of living with trauma and guilt and shame i finally broke free. 
i had been motivated many times to tell my “other” story. in fact i’ve even been pushed by many of you for the last 4 years to go public with what had happened in my life.  especially during the #metoo movement. 
what was happening was i was afraid to give myself permission to speak my truth. i’m in a place now, where i have to give myself the permission to tell you that i went through some pretty severe trauma from being raped at a very young age of 13 years old. then i was raped again in college.  and i lived with it in the dark for almost a decade.  but i know i’m not a victim. and i know that i am stronger because of it.  it took me a long time to learn and understand that. it took therapy and a shit ton of yoga, and different healing practices and it took getting sober. it also ruined countless relationships, jobs, opportunities, because i was just in so much pain and felt so incredibly alone and lost and responsible. and i realize how easily those feelings can get triggered.  i tell myself i’m not attached to those feelings but here’s the deal. sometimes i just feel fucking lonely. sometimes all i want is someone to wrap their arms around me and say, “you got this.” i hope i continue to connect with all of you out there, to help heal others in the ways i know how, and to continue to do what i love. i know that’s why i’m here. and now i’m ready and i give myself permission to be myself and tell you my stories.  because helping others and creating a space for you to heal, also creates a space for me to heal as well.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
“due to a lack of education among teens, they often have trouble identifying toxic behaviors in relationships. girls don’t realize that they can say “no.” also, the abuse is often more controlling and emotional versus physical, making it difficult to recognize. it’s much easier to identify abuse when you’re thrown down a flight of stairs as oppose to someone following you around all the time and checking your cell phone.” “the social media piece can make it even more difficult to identify. social media is so new and as a whole we’re all trying to figure out appropriate boundaries. parents of teens never had boundaries set with social media because it wasn’t around, so they don’t know what guidance to give- like how much time is ok to spend on it. the teens themselves might be so immersed in social media that the idea of not posting their location everywhere they go can seem strange. they might not know that it’s ok to keep passwords private and that it’s not ok to monitor their significant other’s pages constantly.” jen k., children’s counselor at dap y

ou can get in touch with the children’s counselor through the hotline at 610-565-4590 or through your school staff. 
are you interested in having dap’s outreach education specialist speak at your high school, college, business or community organization to provide preventative education on domestic violence and available resources to victims? call dap’s main office at 610-565-6272 or email npowell@dapdc.org for more information. 
#teendvmonth #loveisrespect #breakthecycle #timeisup #loveshouldalwaysbesafe #metoo #startheconversaton #dontjustwatch #dapdv2019 #delawarecountypa #mediapa #loveisnotabuse

text:
part of my job is walking alongside of individuals as they face the evil that has been a part of their story. with trembling boldness they look into the face of destruction, and make a decision not to live in the darkness of the secrets. it’s crazy cool to be around someone with that kind of courage. they are unsung heroes. shame and fear and doubt silenced them. but in this bold, fierce vulnerability there is a rising i get witness. it’s quiet, and unstoppable... the freedom rises. the power the evil held weakens, and truth gets wings. we can do it. we can face the dark, scary things. there is hope beyond the vulnerability. there is a rising. i’ve seen it. 
#trauma #metoo #yourenotalone #arising #therapyhelps #unsungheroes

text:
i’m more than a date
i’m more than a fuck
more than potential
more than a quick buck .
i don’t cease existing
when you don’t need me 
i have my own wants
i have my own needs

i am not your plaything 
don’t toss me away
when it’s clear that “no”
is a word that i say

if you can’t come to me
with friendship, with care
with more than just requests
then do not you dare

don’t you come at me
with “pleases” and “why”s
if that’s all you have for me
don’t waste my time

but if you can see past 
my body, my face
to the soul inside me
then come, take your place .
‘cause friends i will welcome
with arms open wide
and i think you’ll like 
having me by your side

so next time you’re thinking
“she’d look nice in bed”
i hope you’ll think back
to the words that i’ve said:

we are all people;
not here just to please
and if you think we are,
you’re part of the disease

journy 
https://pan-ostic.blogspot.com

#poetry
#morethan
#metoo
#friendswelcome
#assholesbeware

text:
did you know it’s @lgbthistorymonth in the uk? a month for the lgbt community and its supporters in britain to re-claim their history, celebrate the present and create a collective and all-embracing future! _
i am privileged and proud to have many gay friends and many straight friends; to have yellow friends, black friends, brown friends and white friends; to enjoy women friends, man friends, and most of all, dog friends! and you know what they all mean to me? love, truth and luminosity! _
so to everyone in the light, embracing diversity and fighting against marginalisation, i say this: may your day (week/year/life!) be off the hook!! _ p.s. this post is dedicated to a lovely woman i know who wrote to me this morning about her trans child. xx

thank you @rosycheeksrosie , jeds and our ispeak team for all that you put into this work. this is world changing stuff.

text:
________________________________________человек спросил у жизни: - почему я так живу? постоянно завишу от мнения окружающих, не уверен в себе…

и жизнь ответила ему: - ты живешь, чтобы тебе завидовали. а жить нужно так, чтобы вдохновлялись твоим примером. вот тогда ты и будешь счастлив.******************************на щеках - капли счастья,
а в душе - теплота.
спасибо,
что ты такой настоящий,
что верна так рука. 
ты не прошел мимо,
остановился
у старухи со слезливыми глазами
и дрожащей рукой. 
ты подарил мне
букет этот чистый,
согретый теплом
и твоей добротой. 
спасибо за цветы эти вешние,
неоценимые обычной ценой.
я люблю тебя нежно,
я вдохновляюсь тобой.  светлана кладовщикова

text:
when the outside is pristine and the inside is a mess, and the pieces finally start to find their places. when all that remains of your pain is a dark spot on your heart that resembles the edges of blackened and burnt paper. when you see those jagged edges for the beauty they've etched into your face, and the words no longer rage with fury as they leave your mouth.
.
.
.
.

text:
🌟obedience to god’s call🌟

the most meaningful, profound & impactful work i have ever done in my life was being obedient to god’s call to start a support group for adult survivors of childhood sexual abuse. when i was going through my own journey to heal & god said, “heal & be healed,” i never anticipated the overwhelming joy & gratitude i would feel to witness my testimony & obedience bring someone else out of their bondage to freedom....and at the perfect time....👉save someone’s life. 🤯😍✝️🙏🏼😭 🚀what i feel inside is out of this world.🚀 i faced my deepest fears. jesus met me in my most intimate & darkest place. he showed me what i had masked with drugs & alcohol. he helped me release the layers of shame, anger, guilt & embarrassment & lifted the burdens that were never mine to carry. revelation after revelation. he showed me the lies i once believed & spoke his truth into me. 🕊 “the truth set me free.” john 8:32 🕊

now, jesus works through me to heal others. on sunday, i will be standing alongside my sisters in christ & preaching the sermon @ church to shine his light & share what god has done through our first journey to heal support group in ny. 
what a journey! 🛡
what a life! ❤️
what a love is jesus christ! ✝️ is god calling you to take action? face your fears? take a leap of faith? i can tell you wholeheartedly, everything you could ever dream & more is on the other side of fear...answer the call. your blessings await..🥰 #journeytohealministries #metoo #jesusheals #iamdeeplyloved

hrithik roshan’s super 30: anurag kashyap to take care of post-production after director vikas bahl gets ousted following #metoo allegations
#
actor hrithik roshan starrer super 30 will now be helmed by director anurag kashyap. the film has originally been directed by vikas bahl. however, after he stepped away from the film following the #metoo allegations against him, there was no one to look after the post-production work of the film. now, kashyap has confirmed that he will take care of the rest of the film, albeit without taking any credit for it.in his statement to huffpost india, kashyap said that he has taken over the film out of responsibility and only after bahl himself agreed to it. the director was quoted by the website saying, “at the moment i am getting womaniya (another production) started, but yes, i will be overseeing the post-production of super 30. there are at least 30 new people debuting with this film. it’s just out of responsibility for the money put in production.”he also refuted the rumours of having gone back to the same route of friendship with bahl. he said such speculations are nothing but “utter crap”. vikas bahl/ super 30 poster super 30 was initially slated to hit the screens on january 25, facing a box office clash with kangana ranaut starrer manikarnika: the queen of…

text:
the #faxx are in: it’s that time of the month (in march 2019!) why is this important? a plan international uk survey found half of women in the 18-34 age bracket believed an emoji would help them talk about periods. representing menstruation as an international symbol alongside many other ordinary life events and objects could also make a dent in what’s called “period poverty”, which the independent recently reported causes 49% of girls to miss a day of school, and prevents 1 in 10 women aged 14 to 21 from being able to afford period products. it can also go to normalizing the entire experience of being a woman if it’s less and less taboo the more the conversation is out in the open. .
.
.
.

text_retweet:
thank you so much to @kindnessunlimited for publishing this profile!
・・・
i was born and brought up in the us and was lucky to have had so many privileges growing up. however, not everyone is as lucky and that is something i realized early on in life. hence, i started “gyaan ghar” learning centre at the age of 15, which is a tutoring centre located in ludhiana, punjab that provides extracurricular instructions to low-income students in new lajpat nagar. while growing up in the us, i used to arrange a fundraiser in school every year, where if each student donated 5 usd, which is somewhere around 350 indian rupees, it could help run the learning centre for an entire year! this made me realize that it doesn’t take much, to just reach out and put in a little effort to help someone in some way.
we started off with 10 students and today, we have 65 students enrolled, with two full time teachers and amazing volunteers who also act like extra-curricular instructors on a daily basis. of course none of this would have been possible without my grandma who is the de facto principal of #gyaanghar and oversees the daily functioning of the centre. even at the age of 80, she does it with so much gusto and enthusiasm! it is her commitment to creating a change in the community that drives me to do the same as well.
.
after completing my graduation in economics from @harvard, i moved to india to work with @aangan_trust, a nonprofit organization dedicated to reducing child harm in the forms of trafficking, early marriage, labour, and violence. i have a deeply personal passion for working on making women and children safer. especially with the #metoo movement all around us, it feels really important to lend a voice to those who may not even have the visibility to say “me too.”
.
i believe that those of us who are lucky enough to be born with privilege have a responsibility to lift others up with us.
.
#kindnessunlimited @ludhianaliveofficial @make_repost

text: the only way to get powerful answers is by asking powerful questions. the most powerful question i have ever asked myself is am i happy? my answer was no, so that’s when i changed it. don’t overthink things. keep a smile on no matter what. always remember to find your person, tell them everything. at the end of the day they will love you unconditionally. today was a good day! who would have known the ugly duckling is now a beautiful swan. #transformation #positive #transformyourbody #transformyourmind #transformyourlife #weightlosstransformation #beautiful #behappy #motivationmonday #metoo #metoomovement

text:
a snippet from "elizabeth's metoo story part 1"

if you would like to share your story please get in contact of course information will be kept annoymous if wanted 💕

elizabeth had her drink spiked twice  while there. once a lovely group of young guys and girls from ireland found her and took her back to her apartment. close call. thankfully there are still good people around. 
the second time she was not so lucky.
elizabeth had been called over to an older man sitting at the bar about a job opportunity. he asked her what she wanted to drink, he said he was the owner of the club they were in, the bartender agreed. she felt safe,said an iced tea please and continued to speak to him about possible employment.

things start to get blurry but she remembers been pawned off on a younger gentleman. he felt safe to her at that time, in her state, but she still did not feel comfortable. work conversation continued as she struggled to stand upright.
do you need a lift home? he
asked her.
no no i'm fine, she insisted.
who was she kidding she could barely stand nevermind walk.
her friends were gone. where were they is all she kept thinking.
are they not wondering where i am?
they left the nightclub, the light of a new day was not creeping in, well no not creeping in, it was there, set and ready for the day.
she started to wonder what time it was,how was it this bright?

the mans car was directly outside the club. a white convertible. she remembers little details. he told her to get in, she did after refusing multiple times. feeling scared and helpless she eventually agreed.
she was still fighting the urge to pass out... they passed the so called club, closed. over he went to an apartment. elizabeth is getting a bit irate now. he calms her down, it's joint with all the staff you will love them. she knew it was a lie but she knew she had to be smart about this to get out alive. her head is in overdrive trying to stay awake and functional and trying to come up with a plan while been led to that apartment block. while been led towards that building she knew she had a fight on her hands, and if she was lucky enough to get out of there alive nothing would ever be the same....
name: She Is Tangled, Not Tamed

text:
welcome @jowenmagturo of @palmaelash to the women of so cal family ❣️
_
she is a young female entrepreneur; a lash artist and teacher. she is hardworking, talented and kind.
_
jowen got started as an entrepreneur very unexpectantly. she was scrolling on ig and thought it’d be cool to get her lash certification. she asked herself, “what if i became one?” after consulting with her parents, they advised her not to make the investment. 
_
jowen did it anyways. she booked her first client two days after completing her lash certification. in preparation, she stayed up all night researching technique and practicing. as a result of her hard work and late nights she has a thriving business and she was able to pay off her lash certification within the first month. 
_
her biggest influences are her parents and she works hard to show them that success is possible outside of a 9-5 everyday. they cautioned her against her initial investment in her business and now they are her biggest supporters. 
_
her big dream is to bring together a group of dentists to travel the world and offer free dentistry to children in need. her original plan was to become a dentist, however now she is looking to create community and change the world in a different way. sometimes, our plans change and it’s important to shift with them. 
_
there are many challenges within entrepreneurship. jowen originally didn’t have a place to set up, however was creative and temporarily used her mom’s daycare room. she is also learned how to communicate and keep boundaries in her business. 
_
@jowenmagturo is no longer an employee, but a business woman
.
.
.
.
.

text_retweet:
#repost @muslimahideologis.id
• • •
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks .
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). #muslimahnews #muslimahnewsid 
#khilafahajaranislam 
#selamatkanperempuan
#tolakruupks 
#islamsolusinegeri #muslimahideologis

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided repos about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
"then there's me, i'm seventeen
and looking for a fight
all my life i was never there
just a ghost running scared
here our dreams aren't made-
they're won.
lost in the city of angels
down in the comfort of strangers
i found myself in the fire burned hills
in the land of a billion lights
bought my fate straight from hell
second sight has paid off well
for a mother, a brother and me"

text:
i’ve hesitated making this post but i feel very strongly it needs to be said. 
today i found out i was involved in a crime. in my local area a man has been going around for months inappropriately filming women in supermarkets. never in a million years did i think this would involve me but today i found out it does. i was devastated. i was mortified. i was embarrassed. i was inconsolably upset. but i instantly started blaming myself. ‘did i somehow make this man think it was ok to do this to me?’
‘is this my fault because i wore a dress to the supermarket?’ ‘did i look provocative?’ stop!!!!!! i hate we are conditioned to believe that a man’s perverted behaviour is somehow a women’s fault. ‘your dress was too short’
‘you were too drunk’
‘you were flirting’  no!!!!!! why are women taught they can’t be too sexy?, they can’t dress a certain way?, they can’t show too much interest?, they can’t walk home at night?, they can’t, they can’t, they can’t. 
why do we have to live our lives based around men thinking they can do what they want? why do we have to worry about giving a man the ‘wrong impression’? this belief system that women are somehow to blame for a man’s behaviour needs to stop. 
to anyone that needs to hear this. you are not to blame ❤️
.
.
.
.
#metoo #womenarenottoblame #itsmenthatneedtochange #standup #changesocialculture #theresalessonineverything #moretoheal #lotsoftriggerstoday #somanylayerstoheal #energyhealing

text:
continuing my research on the #metoo movement... #metoo was popularized by american actress alyssa milano, on twitter in 2017. milano encouraged victims of sexual harassment to tweet about it and "give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem". there were other hashtags that were in use too  #youoksis, #whatwereyouwearing and #survivorprivilege. 
i think it's mind-blowing "the magnitude of the problem" that has come out since.  it's not just about sexual abuse - it's about all the things that we have considered normal and although we felt uncomfortable, we have put up with it.  it's now okay to rebrand that feeling or episode in our life as wrong and not our fault. and to call it out if it happens again.

text:
признаться, я в тупике. чем старше я становлюсь, тем сильнее мне "жалко птичку". сейчас в сторону отложим геронтологические теории, я предпочитаю называть это "нарастанием эмпатии". к сожалению, в жесткую контру с эмпатией вступает здравый смысл. объясню. .
.
. ‌даже не доходя до вегетарианства, мне противна мысль о выращивании клеточных пушных животных с целью производства меха. альтернативой представляются синтетические материалы - заменители меха (по эстетическим и/или тепловым  характеристикам). ‌но тут в ответ на наши благие намерения мы получаем адские булыжники - полимерные материалы - износостойкие, малоокисляющиеся, долговечные - в таком же неизмененном виде, по крайней мере хиимически - как их задумывали  создатели, - поступают в окружающую среду, преимущественно в виде микро и нано частиц. и заполняют живые организмы, ландшафты,  океан. с чудовищной скоростью. конечно, они не причиняют животным тех немедленных страданий, антропоморфизируя  которые, мы можем ощутить  сочувствие к животным. нет. они работают тоньше. и опаснее. обывателю трудно объяснить, как может быть опасно то, чего он не видит. зато то, что он видит и до понимания чего его сердце уже доросло - до вида несчастных (я не иронизирую - ужасно, несправедливо несчастных) ванек-песцов в клетках и их убийства - это и наглядно, и быстро убедительно. .
.

пресловутое уже поколение #миту склонно, как мне кажется, замечать только партер проблемы, игнорируя многочисленную и гораздо более долгоиграющую и могущественную галерку. .
.

предположу, что универсального ответа (как и должно быть в нашем новом дуалистичном постмодерном мире) не существует. но человек так организован, что ему необходимо быть в каком-то лагере.
и я не знаю. не знаю, чью сторону принять. эмпатии или здравого смысла. .
.
.

на картинке одно из моих первых платьев с вставкой из меха, смысл которого был, в частности, в том, что лиса прорастает сквозь человека (+смотри японскую мифологию). .
.

. ‌даже не доходя до вегетарианства, мне противна мысль о выращивании клеточных пушных животных с целью производства меха. альтернативой представляются синтетические материалы - заменители меха (по эстетическим и/или тепловым  характеристикам). ‌но тут в ответ на наши благие намерения мы получаем адские булыжники - полимерные материалы - износостойкие, малоокисляющиеся, долговечные - в таком же неизмененном виде, по крайней мере хиимически - как их задумывали  создатели, - поступают в окружающую среду, преимущественно в виде микро и нано частиц. и заполняют живые организмы, ландшафты,  океан. с чудовищной скоростью. конечно, они не причиняют животным тех немедленных страданий, антропоморфизируя  которые, мы можем ощутить  сочувствие к животным. нет. они работают тоньше. и опаснее. обывателю трудно объяснить, как может быть опасно то, чего он не видит. зато то, что он видит и до понимания чего его сердце уже доросло - до вида несчастных (я не иронизирую - ужасно, несправедливо несчастных) ванек-песцов в клетках и их убийства - это и наглядно, и быстро убедительно. .
.

пресловутое уже поколение #миту склонно, как мне кажется, замечать только партер проблемы, игнорируя многочисленную и гораздо более долгоиграющую и могущественную галерку. .
.

и я не знаю. не знаю, чью сторону принять. эмпатии или здравого смысла. .
.
.

на картинке одно из моих первых платьев с вставкой из меха, смысл которого был, в частности, в том, что лиса прорастает сквозь человека (+смотри японскую мифологию). .
.

😲yeah, really! women sweat too!

whilst we rarely see any fitness posts showing a drop of sweat on a woman working out, we all bloody sweat at the gym!

don’t let getting sweaty stop you from feeling comfortable to train - personally i always give a mental 🙌 to any one working that hard! if you look like you’ve just had a shower when you get off that treadmill, go girl!

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
i really love this picture by @sebsonntag (thank you ☺️) because in this pic i kind of look like my beloved uncle. as a child i adored him so much, because he was the one who always believed in me like nobody else. one day he said to my mother, who was so proud of my brother ♥️ because he won this mathematic-intellectual -competition thing 👏
(and i thought: „man, i will never ever be able to do the same” -everybody who knows me knows- math and me- well, we are no friends. never been, and never will be.)but he said to her: „just wait, one day alicja is going to show us all what she can.“ well, a few years ago my uncle passed away, not even reaching the age of 50. i would love to talk to him today, and telling him, how much this situation and his words influenced my life till now. 
i‘ve decided to share this with you, to show you what i can- i can’t change the world completely, but i can start- somewhere. 
dear humans/ dear parents / dear uncles and aunties / dear grannies and grandpas / dear teachers- tell children that you believe in them! say it to each other, and most important- say it to yourself. 
thank you, big man for believing in me. 
dear men-you are as much important as us- we don’t want ”to stand over you”, we want you to stand beside us !#feminismisaboutequality

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
🌈
‏زینب پیغمبرزاده در برنامه ‎#چشم‌انداز_زنان: دیدگاهی که برای زنان دوجنسگرا وجود دارد  اشتباه و کلیشه ای است که آن ها در نهایت به مردان گرایش پیدا خواهند کرد.
.
‏بنظرم خیلیا تعریف اشتباهی از بایسکشوالا دارن. فکر میکنن یه فرد بایسکشوال حتما همزمان هم با یه دختر هست هم با یک پسر. داشتن تنها یک پارتنر یا بیشتر هیچ ربطی به گرایش نداره این فقط یک انتخابه که طرف چه جور رابطه ای میخواد داشته باشه.
.
‏اختلالات فوبیا نسبت به دیگر گرایش‌های جنسی فقط مخصوص دگرجنسگرایان نیست، متاسفانه انواع این فوبیا خصوصا بای‌فوبیا در بین همجنسگریان غوغا میکنه، و دقیقا با استدلال‌های استریت‌ها و مثال‌هایی مثل تجاوز و پدوفیلیا سعی در توجیه بیماری خود دارند.
.
فوبیا یا ترس مرضی در مورد گرایش جنسی با نفرت و یا ترس بی دلیل از افراد با اون گرایش خاص تعریف میشه، هموفوبیا به اختصار این روزها برای بیشتر این اشکال فوبیا به کار میره، اما تنفر از ترنس‌ها، لزبین‌ها، گی‌ها، بای‌ها و استریت‌ها یک بیماری قابل درمان است.
.
تجربیات شخصی افراد، شنیده‌ها، حدسیات و یا تخیلات و انتظارات انسان‌ها معیار لیبل زدن به یک جامعه و یا گروه خاص نیست، اگر شما یک تجربه بد با فرد بایسکشوال دارید نمی‌توان آن را به کل جامعه بای ها تعمیم داد.
#دوجنسگرا
#lgbt #bisexual #metoo

text:
4 av 5 kvinnor har utsatts för sexuella trakasserier eller övergrepp.

det är så sjukt så jag säger det igen.

4 av 5 kvinnor har fucking utsatts för sexuella trakasserier eller övergrepp! det här är vår vardag, det här är våra liv. det är flickor som inte får vara ifred i skolkorridorerna, tjejer som blir drogade och våldtagna på nattklubbarna, händer innanför trosorna på festivaler och pojkvänner som tvingar sina flickvänner att suga av dom. det är rädslan när mannen kommer hem efter en jobbfest. skräcken av att höra snabba steg bakom sig när man går hem ensam. det är sjukhusbesöken, kvinnojourerna, sms:n på natten till mamma, nedlagda polisanmälningar, kön till vården, samtalen med psykologen, det är alla åren, det är den där natten, det är det.

det som gör att samtyckeslagen och #metoo var ett skitbra första steg men alla andra steg måste vara att minska övergreppen och trakasserierna. det görs genom att ändra attityder om vad som är över gränsen, vad som är samtycke och övergrepp. vad som är skämt eller trakasserier. empati. inkännande. ansvar.

jag förmodar att ni håller med mig om att siffrorna är ovärdiga vårt samhälle och vår tid - och vem ska ändra dom? vem tänker försöka bidra? varför inte du och jag. när? jo, idag verkar väl vara en jävligt bra dag för att förslagsvis prata med söner, kollegor och killkompisar om hur ekonomisk ojämlikhet är en av de främsta förutsättningarna för mäns utbredda våld mot kvinnor eller om sex, fester, alkohol och samtycke. särskilt män som pratar med andra män, det är så jävla viktigt och bra! kom igen vi kör!

有人買了我的書，問我書中的大台宣傳部是什麼東西，因為大台並無一個部門叫「宣傳部」。其實是這樣的，我書中的宣傳部，實指節目部底下的品牌傳播科（creative imaging department)，負責做宣傳。為了在書中易於表達，才簡化了，管它叫宣傳部。

text:
#enjeux2019 - #tontonsaïsaï, #nopiwouma, #metoo, et plus récemment #doyna sont des hashtags qui représentent des mouvements nés pour libérer la parole des femmes face aux violences sexuelles. cette prise de conscience, d’abord chez les femmes, puis les intellectuels et les militants de la société civile dit quelque chose de la profondeur du combat pour les droits des femmes dans notre pays, notamment chez les jeunes.

l’émergence de cette parole symptomatique du ras-le-bol des femmes sur les violences sexuelles récurrentes a connu un déclic avec #metoo, qui faut-il le rappeler, est né en 2007. même si les multiples accusations d’agression et de harcèlement sexuels envers le producteur américain, harvey weinstein, ont fait renaitre le mouvement en 2017. en effet, plus de 80 femmes l’ont accusé publiquement de viol ou de tentative de viol. la vague weinstein a emporté plusieurs autres personnalités aux etats-unis et a donné naissance à d’autres mouvements comme #balancetonporc en #france.

mais face au tollé qui a suscité une vague de ras-le-bol mondial, le succès de ces initiatives semble dépendre du statut de développement économique et culturel du pays. par conséquent qu’en est-il des mouvements africains, notamment du #sénégal ?

le trio magique sénégalais (maslaa, mougn, soutoureu) est le plus grand ennemi de la prise de conscience ou de la dénonciation des maux qui gangrènent notre société, notamment les agressions sexuelles. économiquement, les femmes subissent des situations de séquestrations dues à la dépendance financière.

culturellement, elles sont tenues de garder le silence sur plusieurs points, sinon le poids du jugement de la société leur sera retenu. quand elles osent parler, elles reviennent rapidement sur leurs mots souvent parce que les personnes qui sont censées les soutenir et les accompagner sont les premières à leur jeter la pierre : la manière dont elles sont accueillies chez elles (« tu vas briser la famille ! »), au niveau des autorités (« tu étais habillée comment ? qu’est ce que tu faisais là ?») et même dans les centres médicaux où le personnel médical peut tenir des discours déplacés envers les jeunes #femmes afin de savoir si elles

text:
jos 2016 oli maailmantuskan vuosi, vuodesta 2019 on hyvää vauhtia tulossa toivon vuosi. #metoo-kampanja on kääntymässä poliittisiksi voitoiksi muun muassa suostumus2018-aloitteen myötä. tuhannet koululaiset ympäri maailman ovat lakossa joka perjantai ilmaston puolesta. on valtava ilo nähdä, kuinka moni on valmis asettumaan rohkeasti ilmaston, ihmisoikeuksien ja tasa-arvon puolelle - vastavoimaksi taantumukselle.

nämä ihmiset valavat toivoa muutoksesta ja osoittavat, että parempi maailma on mahdollinen. juuri tällaista rohkeutta maailma kaipaa ehkä enemmän kuin koskaan. siksi olen valinnut eduskunta- ja eurovaalikampanjani tunnuslauseeksi vastavoima taantumukselle.

kiinnostaako kuulla lisää? tervetuloa mukaan vaalistarttiin tiistaina 19.2. kello 17.00 eteenpäin! samalla pääsee katsomaan millainen on uusi 931 eli arthouse cafe kehräsaari. avaamme tilaisuuden kansanedustaja emma karin ja miehet ry:n puheenjohtajan janne salakan kanssa puhumalla tärkeimmistä tavoista edistää yhdenvertaisuutta ensi vaalikaudella. mikä mättää, kun yhdenvertaisuus ei etene? miksi suomi tarvitsee feministisen hallituksen?

nähdään ensi viikolla!

#iiris2019 #vihreät #vihreätnuoret #suostumus2018 #metoo #häirintä #feminismi #ilmasto #ihmisoikeudet #koulutus #tasaarvo #yhdenvertaisuus #vaalit #vaalit2019
